caption: Amazing food, local produce and wine. Awesome people. Support our local small businesses!

SO GOOD. Can't go wrong here. The clam toast IS A MUST. I also had the lamb burger. I have to say I was hesitate about adding the anchovies but the waiter recommended it and I am glad he did. Yum. The place is small but very cute and cozy. Great for a date or catching up with friends.
Awesome place and amazing food! The produce is some of the freshest I ever had.
Always a joy ordering from here, really love what they dish out and the service is even as great. Not to mention, they're reasonably priced too.
Great wine selection and incredible food!

Mediocre and wayyy overpriced for what it is. Got seated 25 mins after our reservation. The appetizers were better than the entrees. The clam toast was the best dish I had. $17 gets you just a few clams and two pieces of toast. Blowfish tails were ok - different. $18 lamb burger is very small and more like a slider, mine was hard and overcooked. The $27 hake dish is a total joke. 2 apps and 2 entrees later, prepare to leave the place $100 poorer and regretting your life decision.
Small nice place. I liked the food. Service was great
Prices are a little high for the area but menu and food was meh. Full bar as well.
It’s a small space, but very welcoming. The food was very good and I wish I had more of it! I recommend this place for brunch and enjoyed their gravlax toast.
Great food and wonderful people. The lamb burger is awesome. The food is a little pricey and the space is tight. Overall great vibe and great quality.
Overpriced food and I got sick afterwards. Some of the staff was stand-off-ish. The place was way too tiny for a restaurant. But cute decor and good drinks.
Extremely gracious service - tempting desserts - always a wonderful environment!
Awesome food and service.
Delicious brunch - lots of house made  ingredients , they only do sunny side up eggs though, which I enjoy🍳 but if you don't then yr sol
Good food and vibes.
A tiny, wonderful restaurant which maintains a wonderful attention to perfectly prepared dishes. No pretense,  just a good vibe all around and a sophisticated kitchen that never fails to delight.
The food is really inventive and well executed. The staff are helpful. They weren't able to seat us at our reservation time and comped a round of drinks.
It lives up to the hype. Excellent creative dishes, great service.
Straight forward tiny little restaurant. We ate by the bar. We had 2 fish dishes, very fresh, fish perfectly cooked, a great place. Strongly recommended!
The food was great but wished they had a main / more options without meat or fish
Great cocktails. Good food - really nice place all round
If you are looking to dine in,  call ahead to see if they have room -- it's a small space! The food was delightful; I tried to clam toast and would certainly order again.
Amazing food every time
Just incredible awesome

Blown away by what I had.  Chicken thighs braised to perfection served in gravy and green beans.  Server behind the bar guided me to two glasses of wine that suited the dish and catered to my asks.  Excited to come back with a bigger stomach!
Fast and friendly service
Overpriced meal but tasty.

This is a cute place with great food and excellent service. I think most of the food is locally sourced(?) It at least tastes very fresh. The dishes are thoughtful and rotate often, and the menu is small enough to fit on one side of paper (which I like). They have a pretty adventurous wine menu as well. The staff seem coordinated and happy, which is not always the case at these kinds of restaurants. It's definitely more expensive than a lot of places in the neighborhood, but you will not be disappointed.

Went here for brunch with a friend and got there right before they opened. Seated right away - wonderful service. The food was fantastic - perfectly poached eggs on greens. And I’ve never had better hash browns. A neighborhood delight!
Great food, great drinks, great restaurant!
Intimate, neighborhood spot that has feel good vibes as soon as you step in. Everything we tried felt fresh and delicious. Highlights were the clam toast and the lamb burger with anchovies.

Feels like manhattan. In Clinton hill/Bed-Stuy. Make a reservation on a night that you assume will be busy because this place is BUSY. Cute spot, very cozy, because it is the size of a large bedroom. Literally seats maybe 20ish people.  The menu is a small one because the kitchen is probably the size of a closet, but a well-equipped one.  Small plates will run you around $12-$16, entrees $18-28ish.  Drinks selection is big.  My pic attached is the clam toast. Totes delish. Might have to come back just to have this again honestly!! Wish there was more on the plate!

A little too intimate, Hart's could really benefit from having one less table. Luckily the food helps you overlook the cramped space.  The menu is composed of a mix of small and large dishes that lend themselves well to sharing. Because it's ever changing however, I won't go into specifics as beloved dishes might be gone on subsequent visits.  I will say however that the small plates are generally more hit or miss, so I definitely advise to ask the friendly wait staff for their recommendations.
Tiny gem in Bedstuy-ish area, amazing food, and place has a great feel. Waiters were super friendly, as well
Delicious Mediterranean food. Pricey but great for a date night or special occasion.
Consistently the best food to have in Brooklyn. Don't skip it.
Had a blast!

This was such a Great grocery store. So sad it went out of business 😩😭 Very convenient for downtown folks. Very walk friendly. Hope another grocery store moves in soon. Downtown Rochester NY will be lost.

Before we went to NYC, owner of our bnb had recommended Hart’s to us. Actually it’s in the neighborhood so we passed by it a few times when we walked from our bnb to the subway station.  It looked like an interesting place for fine dining therefore we decided to give it a try. The restaurant was small and easily full. Table reservation became a must. Eventually we had a fantastic night there. Food was excellent.  Ambience was stylish and cozy. They also had a good selection of wine!!
Hart’s has a unique menu that constantly changes. The serving staff is trendy and friendly. Food is great, drinks are great, and overall has great bang for buck. Highly recommended for date night.
Great coffee and drinks. Brunch here is perfect if you're looking for something more than avocado toast
Small, intimate restaurant, pricy but excellent food and wine. Achieves the rare trick of having clearly audible music that doesn't drown conversation.
Great wine, tasty food. Didn't have any mains, but tried all the appetizers.
Sooo good!
Love it
Cozy and intimate. food+ service all on par!
Love the clam dust!!!

I’ve gotten off the Franklin C at least once a day for the past year and never thought to come in here. I did today and am so happy that i did. Nice relaxed Music and Atmosphere. We had the Lamb burger witch was probably one of the best burgers I’ve ever had. Must try!
Great food, great cocktails, great staff--and only a block away from where I live, so great location too!
excellent!
While the space is small and tight, the ambiance is nice. The food is great with a Mediterranean French/Italian feeling and the wine selection is very interesting.
Surprised me positively multiple times in one dinner.  The clam toast sounds boring but is delicious. And who puts garlic on a Burger? Geniuses.
Try the clam dust!

5-Star drinks, food, atmosphere and service. It’s the perfect date night spot that won’t break the bank.  For the 1-2 punch, make a reservation or put your name in at Hart’s then head down to Doris’ backyard  for a pre-meal drink.  Menu is rotating, but we had the squid appetizer, pork Milanese and the rock shrimp entrees. The sourdough bread is to die for. Order everything!!

You will not get full off this rabbit Mediterranean food. Had the $16 clam toast that was delectable! Place is cramped, overpriced, not much selection.  We went to a place afterwards,  an African Restaurant for our entree. The service at Harts is beautiful. Waitress was attentive,  explained items and I appreciate that!
Go ahead and order the whole menu, you won't regret it.

Just amazing! The food here is out of this world, and the service is super attentive and accommodating. They answered all of our many questions, made recommendations, and were very kind and sweet. It’s a little gem hidden under the train platform with a very cozy atmosphere.
Great ambiance and vibe w/ 90’s r&b jams in the background. One of the best meals we’ve had in NYC. The apps are where it’s at. Get the clam toast! Drinks are high quality and affordable.
Delicious meal and warm fun service, always a delight!

Outstanding bread and starters. The place has a wonderful charm. Would've been perfect if our waiter hadn't been unfriendly and inattentive - even getting water refilled took a couple tries. Also, there is not one vegetarian entree option. Bit odd.

6 of us, including a baby, had a delicious dinner here. A small friendly neighborhood place. Nick cooks up a storm in the small kitchen. Service is on the slow side. Tried the orange wine which was too bitter for us so had a bottle of red and some ok cocktails. Everyone's food was tasty with good flavors. Come, be patient and enjoy!
Not only one of the best restaurants in Brooklyn or NYC but perhaps the entire world for what they do. I been here 5 times or more. All great, nice compact wine list and good cocktails. No negatives.
Insanely good. Period!
Excellent food, service and wine selection. Cozy but big heart kind of kitchen. The clam toast is a must. Definitely going back.
Understated place with great food and friendly service.
Very good food. A little pricey.
Best brunch in Brooklyn

A favorite neighborhood spot. The food is outstanding, derived from well-selected fresh ingredients and the wonderful use of Mediterranean spices that evoke great flavors from those ingredients. The staff is kind and friendly and the service great.

Cute, intimate restaurant - they have maybe 8 tables and a 5-seat bar, so wouldn’t advise coming here with a big group. Food was tasty, although flavors weren’t particularly unique or groundbreaking. I ordered the clam toast, lamb burger with anchovies, and olive oil cake. Clam toast was essentially a very garlicky moules marinieres over thick-cut, grilled She Wolf Bakery bread. Lamb burger was very good, with a nice savoriness thanks to the anchovies. Olive oil cake was disappointingly dry and crumbly. Service was good, but a little distant, and portions were tiny. Probably won’t come back but it’s worth a try.
Wow.  Everything is amazing - cocktails, radishes, ricotta, head-on shrimp....  Save room for the wonderful olive oil cake.

Attractive room - inventive use of small space. Creative food that honors the ingredients, not afraid of big flavors, intense spicing. I like their use of anchovies and sardines in unexpected places, such as grass fed lamb burger with anchovies. Love this place.
Great brunch! Came here at 1130 on a snowy Sunday and sat immediately. Cozy little place near the subway.
Amazing food. Loved the egg sandwich. Recommend getting a side of fried potatoes. Service was great. Love Hart’s and can’t wait to come back!
Perfectly located, tasteful interior, decor and ambience. The food menu is top for the area. I recommend this for date nights not casual nights jn the area.

Good food, very attentive service. Best thing we ate: the appetizers, ricotta with pesto and hazelnuts, and romanesco with yogurt. Entrees were fish-based and satisfying. The staff comped us an apertif for our anniversary, very nice.
It's just ok overall
Fantastic Sunday brunch with lovely staff and a worthy Bloody Mary.  Lamb burger is the go if it's your thing.
Absolutely fantastic food. Their lamb burger is something I dream about on occasion. Very cozy, small, occasionally crowded (for good reason), very friendly.
Great food and cocktails. Only been once, but will definitely be back.
Super tasty - great wine - bit pricey.
Great food, furendly staff. The seared tuna was incredible.  Only issue with the place is how loud it gets. Some baffles on the celieng or walls would help a lot.

Fantastic meal start to finish. Mussels with heirloom tomatoes as a fresh start. Chicken with lima beans offering a rich umami flavor. Olive oil cake with a perfectly moist crumb. Paired with well-mixed drinks and Mediterranean wines and you are in for a lovely evening.
Good service, good but not great food.
Fried chicken was amazing
Really tasty food, as expected. The space is small but cozy.

Today's we just had dinner  at this restaurant, as a valentine's day celebration. And sadly we are deeply disappointed. The place it's nice but uncomfortable, small tables and seats. Even though the staff was very nice and attentive, the food is completely overpriced and overrated.  We had been at fancy, trendy restaurants and a lettuce salad  needs to be a lot more than just lettuce, some turnips and a dressing to be a 10 dollars or so salad. The prawns where very tasty, but come on guys! We spend nearly 100 dollars on raw carrots and fennel, bread, prawns and lettuce. Not even dessert! There where nice, but no way a 100 dollar nice. After the experience, we left with the bitter taste of being on an mise en scène of a restaurant than a real dinning experience. Tasty, well served but completely unsatisfactory.
Great food and service!!
Lia and staff are amazing!!!!
very impressed for such a small place. food is amazing. Clam toast was off the hook, very interesting. definitely a great spot to come back to.
Incredibly inviting and cozy spot nestled behind stairs to the franklin ave subway. Food was delicious, Service impeccable, and cocktails were cool. I will 100% be coming back.
Delish! Great atmosphere and great service! I will be back.

This restaurant is a slam dunk. The staff is friendly and laid back while providing top-tier service and expertise. The menu is creative, the space is beautiful and the food will keep you talking about it for days. The wine list and cocktails were also remarkable.

I can't say enough about the creative food here. Also, the owners and wait staff are fully engaged and committed to your dining experience, which I promise will be excellent.  The menu is simple and perfect; it's a well thought out choice of foods accompanied by a thoughtful, nontypical wine and cocktail menu. I thought I'd had a lamb burger before coming here--I was wrong. It was so, so good. Fennel on a burger? I didn't know it was perfection!  I've got to try the mushroom ricotta the next time I go.  Then I'll try the swordfish on my next trip. So glad they're right around the corner here in Bed Stuy!

A magical addition to the neighborhood! This restaurant is the type of place where you can take anyone--your grandma, your date, your best friend. A simple menu that's done right (run, don't walk, for the clam toast), in an environment that plays basically the best music while allowing you to actually have a conversation.  I can't wait to go back.
